<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,919,1124]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,919,944]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Watson" authorityYear="1957" box="[408,577,920,944]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermopasta">
<emphasis box="[408,577,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">T. thermopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from other species in the same species group in that the forewing and the posterior half of the hind wing are irrorated with dark scales. In the male genitalia, the uncus is nearly rectangular.
</paragraph>
